INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (51,1,'2021-09-22 10:46:53','2021-09-22 10:46:53','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ridhika\'s team is entirely youth-led and is growing! If you want to volunteer with us, collaborate with us or work with us in any way, follow us on <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/ridhika/\">LinkedIn</a> and email us at <a href=\"mailto:contact.ridhika@gmail.com\">contact.ridhika@gmail.com</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That said, here\'s our diverse team. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>Ian Matindi - Director of Operations</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":79,\"width\":245,\"height\":184,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost:10008/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/DSC4719-1-edited-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-79\" width=\"245\" height=\"184\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ian Matindi studied Economics and Finance at Kenyatta University. He is from Nyeri and helps oversee Ridhika\'s daily operations, including partnerships, Ridhika\'s after-school program and bootcamp. Ian is also involved in the training of new volunteers and teaches our students content on Leadership and Design Thinking. Ian loves to write and in his free time enjoys listening to music and playing basketball. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. <strong>Stephen Muriithi - Director of Technical Development</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":80,\"width\":214,\"height\":299,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost:10008/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/passport_shot-732x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-80\" width=\"214\" height=\"299\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Stephen Muriithi is an embedded software engineer. He graduated from Dedan Kimathi University of Technology with a degree in Mechatronic Engineering. Kairu loves programming and leads the technical development of Ridhika\'s programming curriculum. He has been involved in a variety of projects including android apps, a digital speed governor and biometric systems. An avid builder, Kairu loves delving deep into programming concepts and enjoys sharing his love for programming just as much as he loves to code. Beyond leading the curriculum development of Ridhika\'s programming content, Kairu is involved in the training of our new volunteer teachers. He enjoys watching Spongebob in his free time, runs a blog and is considering starting a YouTube channel.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. <strong>Samuel Kamau - Executive Director</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":81,\"width\":229,\"height\":229,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost:10008/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Myself-color-1024x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-81\" width=\"229\" height=\"229\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Samuel (Sam) Kamau studied Economics and Computer Science at Middlebury College. He is passionate about leveraging technology to solve problems. This passion has translated into inspiring young people across East Africa to use technology to solve their own communities\' problems, starting in his hometown of Nyeri. Sam oversees Ridhika\'s overall strategy, is chairman of its board of directors and helps in spreading Ridhika\'s vision of creating the next generation of innovators across the initiative\'s stakeholders. Sam has been featured on Promazo\'s Top40 Students, has been selected by Middlebury as a Social Entrepreneurship Fellow and noted by the Clinton Foundation as a changemaker for his work in starting and expanding Ridhika. In his free time, Sam enjoys reading, listening to music and playing basketball. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Our Team','','publish','closed','closed','','our-team','','','2021-09-24 13:06:29','2021-09-24 13:06:29','',0,'http://localhost:10008/?page_id=51',0,'page','',0);
